The National Environmental Authority will have the responsibility for decision making and to guide the Executive Coordinating Office. This body will be responsible for:
* Setting policy direction for the REDD+ programs with advice from the Consultation Body;
* Providing guidance and instructions to the Environmental Fund;
* Financial management systems and incentives related to climate change;
* Liaise with international bodies relevant for REDD+ implementation, in particular the UNFCCC Secretariat;
* Oversee benefit sharing criteria and guide the Executive Coordinating Office in this regard.

